I don’t even know where to start.. After a long day with the kids, we decided to go out for a night bite and some drinks. After finding Kyung’s Seafood on Yelp and Google with almost 5 stars we decided to give it a try. First look at the restaurant we were little skeptical since everything is a little outdated. But as the saying goes, “don’t judge a book by its cover”  We got the sashimi platter for $30 and it’s was so so fresh. The cuts were super thick and I can’t believe they give you 27 pieces. Great value!  One of my favorites was the Spicy garlic chicken gizzards. I’ve eating plenty of gizzards but nothing comes close to Kyungs. Perfectly cooked with an abundance of flavor and not over cooked.  The Meat Jun was everyone’s favorite. I don’t recall even having anything close to Kyungs meat Jun. Most places either use cheap meat or over cook theirs. This one just melts in your mouth.  The staff and Auntie Kyung was wonderful. She gave us a sample of her delicious mama special poke. Must try btw! She is the nicest and most genuine lady I’ve ever met. I usually don’t take the time to write such a long review but when the service is that good and the food is amazing. I will always take the time to do so. Like I told you Auntie. “If I could leave you 10 stars I would”  Thank you for the great experience and amazing food  ⭐️ ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

Kyung's is a treasure. Absolutely the best poke I've had, and the rest was delicious too -- mandoos, bbq chicken plates, kalbi, you name it. We also got to spent some time with Kyung herself (some of her very limited down time) as she took a brief break at the back of the place. And she is absolutely wonderful. On top of the good food, her personality is like a magnet. And everyone -- everyone -- knew her and gave her a warm farewell by the time they were leaving. Regulars and newcomers (like us) alike. (She even sent us home with fresh rice for our leftovers and some other supplies to make seaweed snacks out of them.)  Only thing to note is that parking is a bit of a challenge. Come prepared for a lot of circling (knowing the reward will be worth the effort!), or take a cab.
